Project Overview: Art Gallery Management System
Purpose of the Project
To design and implement a relational database system that efficiently manages the operations of an art gallery, including paintings, artists, sections, visitors, and transactions.

Scope of the System

Manage paintings with details like medium, style, price, and status.
Track authors, their biographies, and origins.
Organize paintings into sections within galleries, each managed by assigned staff.
Record visitor logs and daily activities.
Handle transactions for sales and loans, including payment methods and types.
Automate updates and validations using stored procedures and triggers.
Key Features

Normalized schema with 14+ interrelated tables.
Business logic encapsulated in procedures and triggers.
Use of materialized views and indexes for optimized reporting.
Real-world constraints like loan periods, availability checks, and manager assignments.
